Description: Seal-impression made of clay, the back side shows the impression of three rows of basketry coils, the third one shows more than half of the coil which was probably the rim of the basket over which the clay was pressed, the side shows two finger impressions here. The diameter of the basketry rim can be estimated to roughly 10cm. The upper part is roughly flat with the impression of a scarab base, showing a circumferential line, at the right a man standing in a striding position, faced to the left, holding a wAs-sceptre in front of him, the upper part of the figure is not preserved, left of the sceptre a large Shw-feather. Underneath the seal impression an impression of a string is visible as well, 0.3cm in diameter.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
